{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015TJQD3EdyhEgcmW3AiSVRA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've read all three files. Here's what you need to know:\n\n### Admin Auth Middleware (admin.ts, lines 42-48)\n- Simple header check: `X-Admin-Key` header must match the `adminApiKey` environment variable\n- Returns 401 if key is missing or doesn't match\n- Applied to all routes via `app.use(\"*\", ...)`\n\n### Route Registration Pattern (index.ts)\nRoutes are registered in two ways:\n1. **Direct app.route()** - e.g., line 309: `app.route(\"/admin\", createAdminRoutes({ db, adminApiKey }))`\n2. **With middleware first** - e.g., lines 284-288:\n   ```\n   app.use(\"/challenges/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware(...))\n   app.route(\"/challenges\", createChallengeRoutes({ db }))\n   ```\n\n### DB Query Patterns (challenges.ts & admin.ts)\n- All queries use `db.rawSql` with template literals and interpolated parameters\n- Example from admin.ts line 75: `db.rawSql`UPDATE reward_config SET value = ${String(body.value)}, updated_at = now() WHERE key = ${key}``\n- Example from challenges.ts line 125-146: Multi-table JOINs with WHERE/ORDER/LIMIT clauses\n\n### Campaigns & Challenges Relationship\nFrom challenges.ts lines 138-142, the relationship is:\n```sql\nJOIN campaigns camp ON camp.id = c.campaign_id\n```\n- `challenges` table has a `campaign_id` foreign key\n- `campaigns` table has an `id` and `campaign_type` field (e.g., \"daily\", \"weekly\", \"onboarding\")\n- Each campaign can have multiple challenges filtered by `is_active = true`\n\n### Key Config Pattern\n- Admin routes validate against a hardcoded set: `VALID_CONFIG_KEYS` (admin.ts, lines 14-26)\n- Config values stored in `reward_config` table with `key`, `value`, `updated_at` columns\n- Routes query this table for configuration (challenges.ts uses `readRewardConfig()`)"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"423a191d-c5dd-4ced-a84f-1e1163851ef2