{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012MVWJadTSpqKvpGh6jTH4S","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me compile the final report.\n\n## Full Table Definitions and Test Patterns\n\n### SQL Table Definitions from `011_challenge_engine.sql`\n\n#### 1. **campaigns** table\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE campaigns (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  name            TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  campaign_type   TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (campaign_type IN ('daily', 'weekly', 'onboarding', 'dogpile')),\n  starts_at       TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  ends_at         TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  is_active       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true,\n  config          JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**Constraints:**\n- Primary Key: `id` (auto-identity)\n- Unique: `name`\n- CHECK: `campaign_type` must be one of `'daily', 'weekly', 'onboarding', 'dogpile'`\n\n#### 2. **challenges** table\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE challenges (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  campaign_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES campaigns(id),\n  title           TEXT NOT NULL,\n  description     TEXT,\n  action          TEXT NOT NULL,\n  scope           TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'any' CHECK (scope IN ('any', 'coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')),\n  condition       TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'count',\n  threshold       INT NOT NULL,\n  reward_type     TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (reward_type IN ('points', 'crate')),\n  reward_amount   INT,\n  prerequisite_id BIGINT REFERENCES challenges(id),\n  eligible_if     JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  sort_order      INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  is_active       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**Constraints:**\n- Primary Key: `id` (auto-identity)\n- Foreign Keys: `campaign_id` → `campaigns(id)`, `prerequisite_id` → `challenges(id)` (self-referencing)\n- CHECK: `scope` IN `('any', 'coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')`\n- CHECK: `reward_type` IN `('points', 'crate')`\n\n#### 3. **challenge_assignments** table\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE challenge_assignments (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id         TEXT NOT NULL,\n  challenge_id    BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES challenges(id),\n  period_key      TEXT NOT NULL,\n  status          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'active' CHECK (status IN ('active', 'completed', 'expired')),\n  progress        INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  target          INT NOT NULL,\n  assigned_at     TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  expires_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  completed_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  UNIQUE (user_id, challenge_id, period_key)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_assignments_active ON challenge_assignments (user_id, status) WHERE status = 'active';\nCREATE INDEX idx_assignments_period ON challenge_assignments (period_key, status);\n```\n\n**Constraints:**\n- Primary Key: `id` (auto-identity)\n- Foreign Key: `challenge_id` → `challenges(id)`\n- Unique: `(user_id, challenge_id, period_key)`\n- CHECK: `status` IN `('active', 'completed', 'expired')`\n- Indexes: filtered index on active assignments, composite index on period/status\n\n---\n\n### Admin Route Testing Patterns from `integration.test.ts`\n\nThe admin tests demonstrate a clear authentication and request pattern:\n\n**Setup pattern:**\n```typescript\nconst ADMIN_KEY = \"test-admin-key-secret\";\nadminApp = new Hono();\nadminApp.route(\"/admin\", createAdminRoutes({ db, adminApiKey: ADMIN_KEY }));\n```\n\n**Authentication header pattern:**\n- Header name: `X-Admin-Key`\n- Included in all authenticated requests\n- Requests without the header return HTTP 401 with `error: \"UNAUTHORIZED\"`\n- Requests with wrong key return HTTP 401 with `error: \"UNAUTHORIZED\"`\n\n**Request patterns:**\n\n1. **Unauthenticated request (no header):**\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await adminApp.request(\"/admin/reward-config\", { method: \"GET\" });\n   expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n   ```\n\n2. **Wrong key validation:**\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await adminApp.request(\"/admin/reward-config\", {\n     method: \"GET\",\n     headers: { \"X-Admin-Key\": \"wrong-key\" },\n   });\n   expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n   ```\n\n3. **GET request with authentication:**\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await adminApp.request(\"/admin/reward-config\", {\n     method: \"GET\",\n     headers: { \"X-Admin-Key\": ADMIN_KEY },\n   });\n   expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n   ```\n\n4. **PUT request with JSON body and authentication:**\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await adminApp.request(\"/admin/reward-config/points_per_dollar\", {\n     method: \"PUT\",\n     headers: {\n       \"X-Admin-Key\": ADMIN_KEY,\n       \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n     },\n     body: JSON.stringify({ value: \"1000\" }),\n   });\n   ```\n\n5. **Validation testing pattern (400 for invalid keys):**\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await adminApp.request(\"/admin/reward-config/nonexistent_key\", {\n     method: \"PUT\",\n     headers: {\n       \"X-Admin-Key\": ADMIN_KEY,\n       \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n     },\n     body: JSON.stringify({ value: \"123\" }),\n   });\n   expect(res.status).toBe(400);\n   expect(body.error).toBe(\"INVALID_KEY\");\n   ```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- All admin routes require `X-Admin-Key` header\n- Hono app is created with route mounting pattern: `app.route(\"/admin\", createAdminRoutes(...))`\n- JSON responses include `error` field on failures\n- Responses are parsed with `await res.json()` and typed as `Record<string, any>`\n- HTTP status codes follow REST conventions: 200 (success), 400 (validation), 401 (auth failure)"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"423a191d-c5dd-4ced-a84f-1e1163851ef2","uuid":"65d60f72-eb3d-4690-8f10-7289ef4c0d7c","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:24:12.696Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Quick exploration: Read the migration file at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/011_challenge_engine.sql` and report back the full table definitions for:\n1. `campaigns` table (columns, constraints, CHECK constraints)\n2. `challenges` table (columns, constraints, CHECK constraints, foreign keys)\n3. `challenge_assignments` table (columns, constraints)\n\nAlso check the existing integration test file at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` - read lines around where the admin tests are (search for \"admin\" in the test). Report the patterns used for admin route testing (how requests are made, how auth is tested).\n\nReport the complete SQL definitions and test patterns.","agentId":"ae4417e05cc47e53c","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me compile the final report.\n\n## Full Table Definitions and Test Patterns\n\n### SQL Table Definitions from `011_challenge_engine.sql`\n\n#### 1. **campaigns** table\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE campaigns (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  name            TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  campaign_type   TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (campaign_type IN ('daily', 'weekly', 'onboarding', 'dogpile')),\n  starts_at       TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  ends_at         TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  is_active       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true,\n  config          JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**Constraints:**\n- Primary Key: `id` (auto-identity)\n- Unique: `name`\n- CHECK: `campaign_type` must be one of `'daily', 'weekly', 'onboarding', 'dogpile'`\n\n#### 2. **challenges** table\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE challenges (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  campaign_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES campaigns(id),\n  title           TEXT NOT NULL,\n  description     TEXT,\n  action          TEXT NOT NULL,\n  scope           TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'any' CHECK (scope IN ('any', 'coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')),\n  condition       TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'count',\n  threshold       INT NOT NULL,\n  reward_type     TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (reward_type IN ('points', 'crate')),\n  reward_amount   INT,\n  prerequisite_id BIGINT REFERENCES challenges(id),\n  eligible_if     JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  sort_order      INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  is_active       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**Constraints:**\n- Primary Key: `id` (auto-identity)\n- Foreign Keys: `campaign_id` → `campaigns(id)`, `prerequisite_id` → `challenges(id)` (self-referencing)\n- CHECK: `scope` IN `('any', 'coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')`\n- CHECK: `reward_type` IN `('points', 'crate')`\n\n#### 3. **challenge_assignments** table\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE challenge_assignments (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id         TEXT NOT NULL,\n  challenge_id    BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES challenges(id),\n  period_key      TEXT NOT NULL,\n  status          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'active' CHECK (status IN ('active', 'completed', 'expired')),\n  progress        INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  target          INT NOT NULL,\n  assigned_at     TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  expires_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  completed_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  UNIQUE (user_id, challenge_id, period_key)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_assignments_active ON challenge_assignments (user_id, status) WHERE status = 'active';\nCREATE INDEX idx_assignments_period ON challenge_assignments (period_key, status);\n```\n\n**Constraints:**\n- Primary Key: `id` (auto-identity)\n- Foreign Key: `challenge_id` → `challenges(id)`\n- Unique: `(user_id, challenge_id, period_key)`\n- CHECK: `status` IN `('active', 'completed', 'expired')`\n- Indexes: filtered index on active assignments, composite index on period/status\n\n---\n\n### Admin Route Testing Patterns from `integration.test.ts`\n\nThe admin tests demonstrate a clear authentication and request pattern:\n\n**Setup pattern:**\n```typescript\nconst ADMIN_KEY = \"test-admin-key-secret\";\nadminApp = new Hono();\nadminApp.route(\"/admin\", createAdminRoutes({ db, adminApiKey: ADMIN_KEY }));\n```\n\n**Authentication header pattern:**\n- Header name: `X-Admin-Key`\n- Included in all authenticated requests\n- Requests without the header return HTTP 401 with `error: \"UNAUTHORIZED\"`\n- Requests with wrong key return HTTP 401 with `error: \"UNAUTHORIZED\"`\n\n**Request patterns:**\n\n1. **Unauthenticated request (no header):**\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await adminApp.request(\"/admin/reward-config\", { method: \"GET\" });\n   expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n   ```\n\n2. **Wrong key validation:**\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await adminApp.request(\"/admin/reward-config\", {\n     method: \"GET\",\n     headers: { \"X-Admin-Key\": \"wrong-key\" },\n   });\n   expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n   ```\n\n3. **GET request with authentication:**\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await adminApp.request(\"/admin/reward-config\", {\n     method: \"GET\",\n     headers: { \"X-Admin-Key\": ADMIN_KEY },\n   });\n   expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n   ```\n\n4. **PUT request with JSON body and authentication:**\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await adminApp.request(\"/admin/reward-config/points_per_dollar\", {\n     method: \"PUT\",\n     headers: {\n       \"X-Admin-Key\": ADMIN_KEY,\n       \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n     },\n     body: JSON.stringify({ value: \"1000\" }),\n   });\n   ```\n\n5. **Validation testing pattern (400 for invalid keys):**\n   ```typescript\n   const res = await adminApp.request(\"/admin/reward-config/nonexistent_key\", {\n     method: \"PUT\",\n     headers: {\n       \"X-Admin-Key\": ADMIN_KEY,\n       \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n     },\n     body: JSON.stringify({ value: \"123\" }),\n   });\n   expect(res.status).toBe(400);\n   expect(body.error).toBe(\"INVALID_KEY\");\n   ```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- All admin routes require `X-Admin-Key` header\n- Hono app is created with route mounting pattern: `app.route(\"/admin\", createAdminRoutes(...))`\n- JSON responses include `error` field on failures\n- Responses are parsed with `await res.json()` and typed as `Record<string, any>`\n- HTTP status codes follow REST conventions: 200 (success), 400 (validation), 401 (auth failure)"}],"totalDurationMs":18205,"totalTokens":39787,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1426,"cache_read_input_tokens":36735,"output_tokens":1620,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1426},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
