{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RANc63W3xH25j34GjmHMSv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is clear: the `campaigns` table has a UNIQUE constraint on `name`, and the TRUNCATE in `beforeEach` doesn't truncate `campaigns` or `challenges` (they contain seeded data). The campaign names I'm using collide across test runs because the seeded data persists but my test campaigns from previous runs might still exist.\n\nI need to either:\n1. Clean up the test-created campaigns in beforeEach\n2. Use unique names per test run\n\nThe simplest fix is to delete test-created campaigns in beforeEach. But since challenges have FK to campaigns, I should use CASCADE. Let me add cleanup for test campaigns."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1452,"cache_read_input_tokens":79328,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1452},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"423a191d-c5dd-4ced-a84f-1e1163851ef2","uuid":"74d2759e-73c6-413d-8a57-7f229723bcc2"}
