{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015xM7FUU3ojqZWWtRnS2CuB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is that `completion_bonuses` has a FK to `campaigns`, and the DELETE from campaigns fails because `completion_bonuses` still references the seeded campaigns. Since I'm only deleting non-seeded campaigns, this should be fine — the problem is the cleanup is failing on ALL campaigns due to the FK.\n\nWait, the DELETE only targets `WHERE name NOT IN ('daily', 'weekly', 'onboarding')`, so it shouldn't try to delete seeded campaigns. The error is in the beforeEach setup — let me look at the TRUNCATE. The TRUNCATE includes `bonus_completions` but NOT `completion_bonuses`. Since the TRUNCATE uses CASCADE, it should handle it.\n\nActually, the issue is the `DELETE FROM campaigns WHERE name NOT IN ('daily', 'weekly', 'onboarding')` — even though there are no non-seeded campaigns to delete, the error is happening earlier. Let me check what's actually in the campaigns table.\n\nWait — let me re-read the error: `update or delete on table \"campaigns\" violates foreign key constraint \"completion_bonuses_campaign_id_fkey\"`. This means the DELETE on campaigns is trying to delete rows that completion_bonuses depends on. But my WHERE clause should only match non-seeded campaigns...\n\nUnless there are leftover test campaigns from previous runs that now have completion_bonuses rows? That seems unlikely for fresh test campaigns. Let me just add CASCADE to the delete or handle completion_bonuses properly.\n\nActually, the simplest fix: instead of deleting non-seeded campaigns, just use unique test names that won't collide. I'll use a timestamp-based prefix."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":398,"cache_read_input_tokens":86414,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":398},"output_tokens":1,"service